d:3:This document defines the durable business objects and workflow rules for a single story-creation session. The goal is to give the backend, frontend, migrations, and later AI orchestration code one shared contract for how a session progresses, pauses, rewinds, and resumes.\ndocs/domain-model.md:10:- Backward edits are allowed on purpose and must mark downstream outputs stale instead of silently pretending they are still current.\ndocs/domain-model.md:11:- Composition and audio are long-running workflows backed by durable records, not one-shot request responses.\ndocs/domain-model.md:32:| `active_composition_job_id` | Current composition job, if writing or rewrite work is running. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:58:| `composition_job` | Parent job record for writing or rewriting text. | status, progress, attempt count, stop reason, current segment pointer. | Not listed in the prompt title, but needed to make `composition_segment` durable and resumable. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:59:| `composition_segment` | One planned or written segment of the story. | segment index, planned summary, text, revision number, superseded segment, status. | Supports interruption, partial persistence, and rewrites of earlier sections. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:61:| `session_asset` | Durable artifact metadata for session files and exports. | asset kind, object path, MIME type, byte size, checksum, segment index, readiness status. | Covers draft snapshots, composition segments, audio segments, `.docx`, and final audio without scanning object storage. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:77:| 8 | `composition` | Composition | The current story text is complete enough to hand off to narration. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:95:| `in_progress` | Durable work is actively being produced or updated. | Pitch generation is running, composition is streaming segments, or audio rendering is underway. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:96:| `completed` | The stage has an accepted output that is still valid relative to all upstream dependencies. | A beat sheet was accepted and no upstream planning change has made it stale. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:97:| `needs_regeneration` | The stage was completed before, but an upstream change made its accepted output stale. The old output may remain visible for comparison, but it is not the current source of truth. | The user edits characters after a beat sheet exists, so beats, composition, audio, and finalize become stale. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:112:`genre -> tone -> brief -> pitches -> characters -> beats -> story_setup -> composition -> audio -> finalize`\ndocs/domain-model.md:131:| `genre` | `tone`, `brief`, `pitches`, `characters`, `beats`, `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:132:| `tone` | `brief`, `pitches`, `characters`, `beats`, `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:133:| `brief` | `pitches`, `characters`, `beats`, `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:134:| `pitches` | `characters`, `beats`, `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:135:| `characters` | `beats`, `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:136:| `beats` | `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:137:| `story_setup` | `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:138:| `composition` | `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:145:- They still influence later composition, but a new pitch or character sheet does not automatically erase the user's preferred target length.\ndocs/domain-model.md:147:## Composition Interruption and Rewrite Rules\ndocs/domain-model.md:149:Composition is intentionally more flexible than the earlier planning stages.\ndocs/domain-model.md:151:- A composition job may move between `in_progress`, paused, resumed, or cancelled states without leaving the `composition` stage.\ndocs/domain-model.md:153:- A rewrite request against an earlier segment creates a new `composition_job` or new segment revision rather than mutating history in place.\ndocs/domain-model.md:155:- Any accepted composition rewrite marks `audio` and `finalize` as `needs_regeneration`.\ndocs/domain-model.md:156:- If the user decides the plan itself is wrong, they may navigate back to `beats` or `story_setup`, accept changes there, and let the backend mark `composition` and later stages stale.\ndocs/domain-model.md:162:1. Planning session reopened midstream:\ndocs/domain-model.md:165:2. Finished draft reopened for upstream change:\ndocs/domain-model.md:166:   - Example: `composition`, `audio`, and `finalize` were `completed`, then the user edits the beat sheet.\ndocs/domain-model.md:167:   - Result: `composition`, `audio`, and `finalize` become `needs_regeneration`, and `resume_stage = composition`.\ndocs/genre-tone-catalog.md:18:currently include a standalone upstream source file for that catalog. To keep the application\ndocs/segmented-writing-context-carryover.md:3:The composition runtime now treats each outline card as a durable writing segment and carries\ndocs/segmented-writing-context-carryover.md:11:   - Re-assembles the composition prompt package for the active outline card.\ndocs/segmented-writing-context-carryover.md:21:The runtime stores this carryover under `composition_segments.payload.context_carryover` so later\ndocs/segmented-writing-context-carryover.md:22:rewrites can inspect the exact structured input that was used when a segment was generated.\ndocs/segmented-writing-context-carryover.md:28:- Rewrites do not depend on replaying the entire prior draft verbatim.\ndocs/segmented-writing-context-carryover.md:35:Each `composition_segments` row now stores:\ndocs/segmented-writing-context-carryover.md:39:- `accepted_summary`: the compact handoff summary for downstream segments\ndocs/segmented-writing-context-carryover.md:40:- `text_content`: the streamed accepted draft body kept for backward compatibility\ndocs/segmented-writing-context-carryover.md:43:The object-storage side also keeps a `composition_segment` asset per completed segment revision,\ndocs/system-diagram.md:3:This diagram shows the intended runtime shape for Storyteller after the core session, worker, and realtime prompts are built. It documents where session resume, durable event history, realtime delivery, and long-running jobs belong.\ndocs/system-diagram.md:9:    WS[\"WebSocket session stream<br/>replay recent events + deliver live progress\"]\ndocs/system-diagram.md:10:    Worker[\"Worker process<br/>composition jobs, audio jobs, retries, interruption\"]\ndocs/system-diagram.md:13:    Gemini[\"Gemini adapters<br/>planning, composition, narration\"]\ndocs/system-diagram.md:28:    Worker -->|\"planning, composition, TTS calls\"| Gemini\ndocs/frontend-design-foundation.md:54:    aria-label=\"Planning completion\"\ndocs/frontend-design-foundation.md:55:    label=\"Planning completion\"\ndocs/realtime-events.md:1:# Realtime Events\ndocs/realtime-events.md:8:[docs/realtime-events.schema.json](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/realtime-events.schema.json).\ndocs/realtime-events.md:10:[backend/app/models/realtime.py](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/models/realtime.py).\ndocs/realtime-events.md:18:- High-frequency typing chunks stay ephemeral. The UI can feel live without\ndocs/realtime-events.md:23:- Segment indexes are 1-based. `chunk_index` is 0-based within a segment.\ndocs/realtime-events.md:103:- `event_id`: unique realtime-delivery identifier.\ndocs/realtime-events.md:113:  stream hints such as text chunks.\ndocs/realtime-events.md:124:| `composition.chunk` | no | Live typewriter chunk stream for composition. |\ndocs/realtime-events.md:125:| `job.progress` | yes | Progress checkpoint for composition or audio jobs. |\ndocs/realtime-events.md:126:| `job.status` | yes | Queue, start, pause, completion, cancellation, or failure transition for a job. |\ndocs/realtime-events.md:174:### `composition.chunk`\ndocs/realtime-events.md:181:- `chunk_index`\ndocs/realtime-events.md:182:- `chunk_kind`\ndocs/realtime-events.m