/event-taxonomy.md:31:| `content.user_edit.recorded` | Structured user-authored edits to durable planning or composition records. | `user` | stage-specific |\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:34:| `composition.progress.recorded` | Durable composition job progress for replay and worker debugging. | `system` | `composition` |\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:57:  \"invalidated_stages\": [\"pitches\", \"characters\", \"beats\", \"composition\", \"audio\", \"finalize\"],\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:96:- `record_composition_progress(...)`\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:128:event_log.record_composition_progress(\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:130:    job_id=composition_job.id,\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:153:  without re-reading the entire raw event stream.\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:154:- Do not rewrite or delete historical events to \"fix\" history. Emit a new compensating event.\ndocs/product-brief.md:28:8. Composition in segments with visible progress, typewriter-like output, and interruptibility.\ndocs/product-brief.md:52:### Composition Experience\ndocs/product-brief.md:57:- Users can interrupt, redirect, and request rewrites.\nbackend/tests/test_settings.py:51:        settings.gemini.approximate_pricing.composition.output_cost_per_million_tokens_usd\nbackend/tests/test_settings.py:77:            composition:\nbackend/tests/test_settings.py:112:        settings.gemini.approximate_pricing.composition.output_cost_per_million_tokens_usd\nbackend/tests/test_event_log_service.py:85:    event_log.record_composition_progress(\nbackend/tests/test_event_log_service.py:87:        job_id=\"composition-job-1\",\nbackend/tests/test_event_log_service.py:139:    assert history.events[5].stage == WorkflowStage.COMPOSITION\nbackend/tests/test_model_usage_service.py:102:                usage_bucket=ModelUsageBucket.COMPOSITION,\nbackend/tests/test_model_usage_service.py:103:                workflow_stage=WorkflowStage.COMPOSITION,\nbackend/tests/test_model_usage_service.py:104:                purpose=\"composition_generation\"