{"color": "cyan", "emoji": "\ud83d\udee0", "event_type": "Command Finished", "message": "completed, exit 0: /bin/zsh -lc 'rg -n \"session events|realtime|websocket|ws\" infra backend/README.md docs -S'", "raw_event": {"item": {"aggregated_output": "backend/README.md:22:Planned expansion inside `app/` follows the architecture notes in [docs/architecture-overview.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/architecture-overview.md), including explicit homes for repositories, AI adapters, storage, and worker execution.\nbackend/README.md:48:The settings module merges built-in defaults, `secrets.yaml`, and then `STORYTELLER_*` environment variables. Environment variables win when both sources set the same field. The backend-only Gemini key lives in `secrets.yaml` or the backend process environment and is never sent to the browser.\ndocs/storage-buckets-and-prefixes.md:28:That keeps resumable jobs, later cleanup policies, and session-scoped browsing aligned even when\ndocs/storage-buckets-and-prefixes.md:67:bootstrap code in composition, export, or audio workflows.\ninfra/README.md:10:As the stack grows, keep infrastructure concerns here instead of scattering them across the repository root.\ndocs/genre-tone-catalog.md:79:- existing rows are updated in place when slugs match\ndocs/genre-tone-catalog.md:80:- missing catalog rows are marked inactive instead of being deleted\ninfra/compose/docker-compose.yml:157:  browser:\ninfra/compose/README.md:21:- `browser` as the containerized QA runner\ndocs/chat-action-echoes.md:29:- Action echoes render as `action_echo` transcript rows, not assistant prose.\ndocs/realtime-events.md:1:# Realtime Events\ndocs/realtime-events.md:8:[docs/realtime-events.schema.json](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/realtime-events.schema.json).\ndocs/realtime-events.md:10:[backend/app/models/realtime.py](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/models/realtime.py).\ndocs/realtime-events.md:15:- The browser subscribes to one session channel at a time: `session:{session_id}`.\ndocs/realtime-events.md:103:- `event_id`: unique realtime-delivery identifier.\ndocs/realtime-events.md:131:Use this for complete chat content, not previews. Payload fields:\ndocs/realtime-events.md:145:`WorkflowStageChangedEventPayload`:\ndocs/realtime-events.md:282:realtime feed is a delivery mechanism layered on top of that truth.\ndocs/realtime-events.md:302:- The backend treats the current browser as `local-user`.\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:55:        \"ChatMessageRealtimeEvent\": {\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:84:              \"$ref\": \"#/$defs/RealtimeDeliveryMode\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:125:                  \"$ref\": \"#/$defs/WorkflowStage\"\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:150:          \"title\": \"ChatMessageRealtimeEvent\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:270:        \"CompositionChunkRealtimeEvent\": {\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:360:          \"title\": \"CompositionChunkRealtimeEvent\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:434:        \"ErrorNotificationRealtimeEvent\": {\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:463:              \"$ref\": \"#/$defs/RealtimeDeliveryMode\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:504:                  \"$ref\": \"#/$defs/WorkflowStage\"\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:529:          \"title\": \"ErrorNotificationRealtimeEvent\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:727:              \"$ref\": \"#/$defs/RealtimeJobStatus\"\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:764:        \"JobProgressRealtimeEvent\": {\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:793:              \"$ref\": \"#/$defs/RealtimeDeliveryMode\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:834:                  \"$ref\": \"#/$defs/WorkflowStage\"\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:859:          \"title\": \"JobProgressRealtimeEvent\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:937:                  \"$ref\": \"#/$defs/RealtimeJobStatus\"\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:952:              \"$ref\": \"#/$defs/RealtimeJobStatus\"\ndocs/realtime-events.s